    "Multi-layer Perceptron (MLP).",
    "An MLP generally consists of an input layer, hidden layers, and an output layer, formulated as follows:",
    "MLPs consist of multiple layers of nodes in a directed graph with each layer fully connected to the next layer.",
    "Their computational costs depend on the number of layers and nodes per layer.",
    "However, time-series forecasting might require manual feature engineering, which can add to the overall processing time."
